<TITLE> India has right to protect itself: foreign minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Dec 02 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Foreign Minister Pranab Mukherjee on Tuesday said his country reserved the right to take military action if its territory was under threat. "I am neither making any comment on military options. What I am saying is every sovereign country has its right to protect its territorial integrity and take appropriate action as and when it feels necessary," Mukherjee told NDTV.
